
[1]patronymic

   PATRONYM'IC, n. [L. patronymicus; from Gr. father, and name.]

   A name of men or women derived from that of their parents or ancestors;
   as Tydides, the son of Tydeus, Pelides, the son of Peleus, that is,
   Achilles.
